No, this guide isn't about Hasbro's family board game hit "The Game of Life", nor, 
unfortunately, the secrets that may underlie the true game of Life itself —
rather, it's about [mark]mathematician John Conway's 1970s brainchild[/mark] that captured the minds 
of many professional and amateur players alike. 
And while his creation doesn't quite contain the answer to *Life, the Universe and Everything,*¹ 
it *does* provoke some tantalizing questions about [mark]how complex phenomena can emerge from simplicity[/mark] 
and about the rules that may (or may not) govern our world.
