## What you'll learn

In this interactive guide, we'll be going though a basic introduction to John Conway's Game of Life. 
We'll explore where it came from, define exactly what it is, and examine some of its fascinating characteristics.
This guide consists of six lessons in all:

[DropDown items:`[
  { "heading": "Lesson 1: The origin of Life", "panel": "What are the intellectual origins of the Game of Life? What is a cellular automaton?"}, 
  { "heading": "Lesson 2: Life begins", "panel": "What was Conway's purpose for creating the Game of Life? How did he do it?"}, 
  { "heading": "Lesson 3: Three simple rules", "panel": "What are the three rules of the Game of Life? (Preview: birth, death, survival)"}, 
  { "heading": "Lesson 4: Classifying Life's organisms", "panel": 'What "creatures" appear in the Game of Life? What are the three most common types?'}, 
  { "heading": "Lesson 5: Life's primoridal soup", "panel": "What are the initial conditions of a system? Why is Life considered a complex system?"}, 
  { "heading": "Lesson 6: Life is universal", "panel": 'What is the meaning behind the phrase "Life is Universal"?'}, 
]` /]
